vi makefile
make
make a2ps
/home/ihlee/csa_vasp/readfort1.x < csa.in

this procedure generates many POSCAR files, such as POSCAR_0001, POSCAR_0002, POSCAR_0003, ....

the number of files is the number of population in the CSA run

grep 'ifort ' *.f90
toposcar.f90:!      ifort toposcar.f90 numeral.f cmds.f

evince toposcar.ps
in vi/vim you can use
:syntax off
:syntax on

Linux/Unix commands:
/usr/local/bin/a2ps ( https://www.gnu.org/software/a2ps/ )
/opt/intel/Compiler/12.1.6/bin/intel64/ifort
/usr/bin/evince
/usr/bin/make
/usr/bin/vim
/usr/bin/nohup
/bin/nice

